81.words: Okay. The place on campus I feel most comfortable meeting others? I chose this one just because at MIT, I feel like I've done a lot of things that are either involved in dance or involved in presentation design or in some way or form showing off something on a stage. And I'm not the most comfortable with going on a stage and being looked at by others because I have some stage fright. But I do find it very comfortable to meet and talk to other performers and people who are familiar with either playing an instrument for a group of people, dancing in front of people, creating art, and then being vulnerable and just putting something that they worked out for other people to see, because a very difficult thing to do. And I think it's valuable when people do that. I played the cello several, several years, and then I came here and I danced for several years and then I've been doing art my whole life.
